Description: Two disc-shaped reused pottery sherds, very well smoothed on all sides, both pierced with two holes in the centre. One of them shows the beginning of a third perforation hole that was not completed. Very thin pottery. Measurements refer to larger piece.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), D15, Mound β
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
